{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:job.13",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 13,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 13",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 13 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:1",
      "text": "Behold my eye hath seen all these things, and my ear hath heard them, and I have understood them all.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:2",
      "text": "According to your knowledge I also know: neither am I inferior to you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:3",
      "text": "But yet I will speak to the Almighty, and I desire to reason with God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:4",
      "text": "Having first shewn that you are forgers of lies, and maintainers of perverse opinions.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:5",
      "text": "And I wish you would hold your peace, that you might be thought to be wise men.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:6",
      "text": "Hear ye therefore my reproof, and attend to the judgment of my lips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:7",
      "text": "Hath God any need of your lie, that you should speak deceitfully for him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:8",
      "text": "Do you accept this person, and do you endeavour to judge for God?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:9",
      "text": "Or shall it please him, from whom nothing can be concealed? or shall he be deceived as a man, with your deceitful dealings?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:10",
      "text": "He shall reprove you, because in secret you accept his person.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:11",
      "text": "As soon as he shall move himself, he shall trouble you: and his dread shall fall upon you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:12",
      "text": "Your remembrance shall be compared to ashes, and your necks shall be brought to clay.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:13",
      "text": "Hold your peace a little while, that I may speak whatsoever my mind shall suggest to me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:14",
      "text": "Why do I tear my flesh with my teeth, and carry my soul in my hands?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:15",
      "text": "Although he should kill me, I will trust in him: but yet I will reprove my ways in his sight.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:16",
      "text": "And he shall be my saviour: for no hypocrite shall come before his presence.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.17",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:17",
      "text": "Hear ye my speech, and receive with your ears hidden truths.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.18",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:18",
      "text": "If I shall be judged, I know that I shall be found just.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.19",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:19",
      "text": "Who is he that will plead against me? let him come: why am I consumed holding my peace?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.20",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:20",
      "text": "Two things only do not to me, and then from thy face I shall not be hid:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.21",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:21",
      "text": "Withdraw thy hand far from me, and let not thy dread terrify me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.22",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:22",
      "text": "Call me, and I will answer thee: or else I will speak, and do thou answer me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.23",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:23",
      "text": "How many are my iniquities and sins? make me know my crimes and offenses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.24",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:24",
      "text": "Why hidest thou thy face, and thinkest me thy enemy?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.25",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:25",
      "text": "Against a leaf, that is carried away with the wind, thou shewest thy power, and thou pursuest a dry straw.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.26",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:26",
      "text": "For thou writest bitter things against me, and wilt consume me for the sins of my youth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.27",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:27",
      "text": "Thou hast put my feet in the stocks, and hast observed all my paths, and hast considered the steps of my feet:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:job.13.28",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 13,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 13:28",
      "text": "Who am to be consumed as rottenness, and as a garment that is motheaten.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
